Stay safe and well.

For our preschool-age students and families - ALL children will be eligible to participate in our SPARK program for the 2020-2021 school year. SPARK (Supporting Partnerships to Assure Ready Kids) is a Kindergarten readiness program where you and your child will work one-on-one with Ms. Michelle two times per month. Children will receive free books, learning materials, and supplies at every lesson; these supplies will be delivered to your home before your lesson time. Lessons will be virtual for the first half of the school year using your choice of Zoom, FaceTime, or Google Duo. Lessons are fun and interactive, lasting around 30 minutes. Please take advantage of this terrific opportunity by completing the Google Form below. If you have any questions, please contact Ms. Michelle at 513-896-7153, ext. 1104 or send a message to the New Miami Mini Vikings Facebook page.

https://forms.gle/AQvu7qJ7ErbCChXF8

Michelle Ewen
Birth-Age 5 Parent/Family Liaison
SPARK Parent Partner
New Miami Elementary School

"Be Better Every Day...Move Urgently, Take Risks, Show Grit"
Go Vikings!

post_text:
As Posted on the High school Facebook Page:

SHUTTLE TO THE GAME! As a convenience to our fans and community and in an effort to alleviate some of the parking concerns we may experience we will be operating a shuttle bus to and from the game on Saturday night.

The shuttle will run from 5 pm to 7 pm before the game and from the end of the game until one hour after the game ends.

The shuttle pickup and drop off points will be along Rt. 127 at the corners of Fox, Elliott, Cain, Morris, and Whitaker, on Augspurger near Roselea, and on Seven Mile Ave. at Whitaker, Morris, Cain, Elliott, and Fox. Fans will be dropped off at the first entrance to our campus on Seven Mile Ave. before the game and will be picked up near the same location following the end of the game.

We hope you will consider using this service rather than driving to the game if at all possible, as we are expecting a large crowd and parking is extremely limited.

Go Vikings!!!

The New Miami Local Schools was on a Level 1 Lockdown (Level 1 Lockdown: exterior doors are locked; use of front lobby doors only; and no outside activities are to occur) this afternoon due to an incident reported in the local area.

Staff and students were in a Lockdown according to our Safety Plans and Procedures.

Butler County Sheriff’s Deputies were on the scene and working closely with New Miami Local School District personnel.

The Lockdown was cleared quickly as authorities lifted the threat for the New Miami Local School.

The safety of our Staff and Students is always a top priority.

post_text:
Head Lice Home Check Reminder for Parents and Guardians:

Please check your child’s head frequently for the presence of lice and/or nits. Head lice have no season, do not jump or fly, and require prolonged head to head contact to spread.

They will die within 24 hours once they are off the head.

Studies have shown that spread is rare within schools, and more commonly occur at camps, sleepovers, household or family contact, and after school activities where head to
head contact is common.

Often the infestations become obvious only after 1 -2 months.

Unless you know of someone with lice, the source can be hard to pinpoint.

WHAT YOU CAN DO
• Check your child’s head at least twice a week, especially if your child complains
of an itchy scalp.
• Keep long hair pulled back.
• Teach your child about personal space and how to avoid situations where his or
her hair makes contact with others.
• Avoid sharing of hats, helmets, or brushes.
• If you have any questions, feel free to contact your school nurse.

Dear Parents,

As the new school year begins, there is nothing more important than providing your child with safe and reliable transportation. We appreciate the opportunity to serve your family.

School buses are the safest way for students to get to and from school. According to the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration, school buses are 70 times safer than passenger cars and 10 times safer than walking.
There is an entire ecosystem of safety around school buses. This includes road signs, traffic laws, the size, weight and construction of the bus, and the skill of the driver.
It also includes you. We encourage you to review school bus safety tips with your children to make the… More
